1. ## **Splinterlands**

Genre: Collectible Card Game  
Token: $SPS  
Play Option: Play-to-earn & Free-to-play

Overview:  
![][image1]  
[Source](https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1001189861317951488/1668113483/600x200)

Splinterlands is a digital collectible card game that takes place in a fantasy world. Players build decks of cards featuring various creatures and monsters, each with their own unique abilities and strengths. The goal of the game is to defeat your opponent by reducing their life points to zero.

At the start of each game, players draw a hand of cards from their deck and take turns playing them onto a 3x3 game board. Each card has a mana cost associated with it, and players must spend their available mana to play their cards.

Cards are divided into six different splinters, each with their own strengths and weaknesses. Players take turns placing their cards on the board, using their abilities to attack their opponent's cards or defend their own. Each card has a certain number of hit points, and when a card's hit points reach zero, it is removed from the board.

In addition to playing cards, players can also use various items and spells to aid them in battle. These include potions that heal damaged cards, spells that deal damage to enemy cards, and items that boost the abilities of friendly cards.

The game continues until one player's life points are reduced to zero. The winner earns rewards such as new cards, items, and in-game currency, which can be used to buy more powerful cards and items to improve their deck.

As players progress through the game, they can unlock new splinters and earn access to more powerful cards, allowing them to create even stronger decks and take on more challenging opponents.

2. ## **Psyber X**

Genre: MMORPG  
Token: $LVL  
Play Option: Free-to-play & Play-to-earn

Overview:  
![][image2]  
[source](https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1292935179334426624/1664203153/600x200)

Psyber X is a fast-paced, action-packed side-scrolling shooter game set in a futuristic world. The player takes on the role of a highly skilled fighter pilot who must navigate through a series of levels, battling against enemy forces and powerful bosses to save humanity from destruction.

The gameplay of Psyber X is divided into various stages, with each stage consisting of multiple levels. Each level is populated by various enemies, including ground-based vehicles, air units, and robotic drones. The player must use their flying skills and arsenal of weapons to defeat the enemies and reach the end of the level.

At the end of each level, the player must face a boss battle against a powerful enemy ship or a giant robot. These bosses are highly challenging and require careful strategy and quick reflexes to defeat.

As the player progresses through the game, they earn points for defeating enemies and completing levels. These points can be used to upgrade their ship, weapons, and special abilities.

3. ## **DCity**

Genre: Card Game  
Token: $SIM  
Play Option: Play-to-earn

Overview:  
![][image3]  
[Source](https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/1441907637784772614/1653276582/600x200)

DCity is a city-building simulation game where the player takes on the role of a city mayor and builds a thriving metropolis. The game features a variety of buildings and infrastructure that the player can construct, such as residential buildings, commercial buildings, and public services.

The gameplay of DCity is divided into various phases, with each phase consisting of a set of goals that the player must achieve in order to progress to the next phase. The player earns money by collecting taxes from their citizens and can use this money to build new buildings, upgrade existing ones, and improve the city's infrastructure.

The game also features various challenges that the player must overcome, such as natural disasters, economic downturns, and crime waves. The player must manage their city's resources carefully, balancing the needs of their citizens with their budget constraints.

DCity also features a variety of customization options, allowing the player to personalize their city and make it unique. As the player progresses through the game, they unlock new buildings, technologies, and upgrades that allow them to build bigger and more complex cities.

4. ## **eXode**

Genre: Real-time strategy Role-Playing Game  
Token: $EXOFUEL  
Play Option: Free-to-play & Play-to-earn

Overview:  
![][image4]  
[source](https://pbs.twimg.com/media/FOsGrcnWYAA85vD?format=jpg&name=small)

Exode is a multiplayer strategy game set in a post-apocalyptic world where players must build their own settlements, gather resources, and engage in battle against rival factions. The game features a variety of gameplay elements, including base building, resource management, and tactical combat.

The gameplay of Exode is divided into various modes, with each mode offering different objectives and challenges. The primary mode is the settlement mode, where players must build and manage their own base, gather resources, and upgrade their infrastructure. The player must also recruit and train a team of soldiers, each with their own unique abilities and specialties.

The game also features a tactical combat mode, where players engage in battles against other players or computer-controlled enemies. The combat is turn-based, with players taking turns to move their soldiers and attack their opponents. Each soldier has a set of skills and abilities that can be upgraded over time, allowing the player to customize their army to suit their playstyle.

The game also features a variety of resources that the player must manage, including food, water, and fuel. These resources can be used to build new structures, train soldiers, and conduct research to unlock new technologies and upgrades.

As the player progresses through the game, they unlock new technologies and upgrades, allowing them to build more advanced structures, recruit stronger soldiers, and access more powerful weapons and equipment.

Wrestling Organization Online is an online wrestling simulation game where players can create their own wrestlers and compete against other players from around the world. The game features a variety of gameplay elements, including character creation, match types, and championship belts.

Players start by creating their own wrestler, choosing from a wide range of customization options such as appearance, moveset, and personality. They can also assign attribute points to their wrestler's various stats, such as strength, speed, and endurance.

Once their wrestler is created, players can compete in a variety of match types, including singles matches, tag team matches, and ladder matches. They can also challenge other players for championship belts, which can be defended in future matches.

As players progress through the game, they can unlock new match types and championship belts, as well as earn achievements and climb the global leaderboard.
